# Drafting Board — environment variables
# Copy to `.env.local` for local dev, or set these in your host's dashboard
# (Vercel: Project → Settings → Environment Variables). Never commit real values.

# Shared stakeholder password for the site-wide gate.
# When UNSET, the password gate is DISABLED (convenient for local dev / previews).
# Set this in every environment you want protected (Production is required).
SITE_PASSWORD=

# Optional extra secret mixed into the session-cookie signature.
# Rotating it (or changing SITE_PASSWORD) invalidates all existing sessions,
# forcing everyone to re-enter the password. Use a long random string, e.g.
#   openssl rand -hex 32
# Safe to leave blank — the password alone still produces a valid signing key.
SITE_SESSION_SECRET=
